Example: A digital camera focuses on a chessboard. Sketch the voltage produced by column 1.2 over time.

Solution: The pixels in each column receive light only from the white squares [Fig. 1.6(a)]. Thus, the column voltage alternates between a maximum for these pixels and zero for those receiving no light. The resulting waveform is shown in Fig. 1.6(b).

