Exercise: Plot the voltage if the first and second squares in each row have the same color.

What does each signal processing block do? Since the voltage produced by each pixel is an analog signal capable of assuming any value within a range, it must first be "digitized" using an "analog-to-digital converter" (ADC). A 6.25 megapixel array requires 2500 ADCs. Given the complexity of ADCs, we may time-share one ADC between every two columns (Fig. 1.7), necessitating the ADC to operate twice as fast. Alternatively, we could use a single, very fast ADC for all 2500 columns. In practice, the optimal choice lies between these two extremes.

